**\n   - Uses `req.StepName` if provided\n   - Otherwise finds first failed step from captures\n   - Returns error if no failed step found\n\n4. **Build Prior Results**\n   - Calls `succeededStepsBefore()` to get all successful steps before resume point\n   - Creates `ResumeConfig` with `FromStep` and `PriorResults`\n\n5. **Dispatch Based on Run Type**\n   - Container runs: calls `resumeContainerRun()`\n   - Host runs: calls `resumeHostRun()`\n\n**Container Resume (`resumeContainerRun`)**:\n- Verifies container still exists via `Inspect()`\n- Marshals `ResumeConfig` to JSON\n- Creates temp file and copies into container at `/workspace/.cloche/resume.json`\n- Copies updated project files (scripts, prompts, overrides) into container\n- Resets run state to `Pending`, clears error message and active steps\n- Calls `restartAndTrack()` to restart the container and track completion\n\n**Host Resume (`resumeHostRun`)**:\n- Creates run-specific directory (`.cloche/<run-id>`)\n- Writes `resume.json` to that directory\n- Resets run state to `Pending`\n- Creates new `host.Runner` and runs the workflow in a goroutine\n\n**Helper Functions**:\n- `restartAndTrack()`: Restarts stopped container via `docker start`, updates run state, tracks to completion\n- `firstFailedStepFromCaptures()`: Exported helper to find first failed step\n- `succeededStepsBefore()`: Exported helper to build prior results map\n- `dockerCp()`: Wraps docker cp for file copying\n- `copyProjectUpdates()`: Copies scripts, prompts, and overrides into running container\n\n**Location: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/export_test.go`**\n- Exports test helpers:\n  - `FirstFailedStepFromCaptures`\n  - `SucceededStepsBefore`\n\n**Location: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/resume_test.go`**\n- Tests for resume helpers:\n  - Finding first failed step from captures\n  - Handling incomplete steps\n  - Getting succeeded steps before target (including skipping failures)\n\n### **6. CLI Integration**\n\n**Location: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`**\n- Added `resume` to `daemonCmds` map for help flag handling\n- Added case statement to route to `cmdResume()`\n- New function `cmdResume()`:\n  - Parses arguments: run-id (required), step-name (optional)\n  - Creates `ResumeRunRequest`\n  - Calls `pb.InvokeResumeRun()` on the gRPC connection\n  - Prints \"Resumed run: {run-id}\" on success\n\n**Location: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`**\n- Added comprehensive help text for `cloche resume` command:\n  - Usage: `cloche resume <run-id> [step-name]`\n  - Describes step-specific behavior (script/prompt/workflow steps)\n  - Prerequisites (run must be failed, container must exist for container workflows)\n  - Examples\n\n### **7. Prompt Adapter Resume Support**\n\n**Location: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go`**\n\nNew `executeResume()` method handles prompt step resume:\n- Adds `-c` flag (conversation continue) to agent command arguments\n- Uses \"retry\" as the prompt instead of full prompt assembly\n- Follows same fallback chain and result classification as normal execution\n- Resets attempt count on success\n- Writes output files normally\n\nResume path is triggered when step config has `_resume` = `\"true\"` (set by `ResumeExecutor`).\n\n### **8. Agent Runner Integration**\n\n**Location: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`**\n- Reads `resume.json` from `.cloche/resume.json` at startup\n- Unmarshals into `domain.ResumeConfig`\n- Removes the file so next run starts fresh\n- Passes to `agent.NewRunner()` via `RunnerConfig`\n\n**Location: `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`**\n- `RunnerConfig` now includes optional `ResumeConfig` field\n- If `ResumeConfig` is provided:\n  - Preserves per-run state (attempt_count, output files)\n  - Wraps executor in `ResumeExecutor` with prior results and resume step\n- On fresh runs, clears attempt_count and output directories\n\n### **9. Daemon Registration**\n\n**Location: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`**\n- Registers `ResumeRunHandler` on gRPC server: `pb.RegisterResumeRunHandler(grpcServer, srv)`\n- The `ClocheServer` implements the `ResumeRunServer` interface\n\n### **10. Container Runtime**\n\n**Location: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`**\n- No changes needed; uses existing `docker cp` and `docker start` commands\n\n**Location: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`**\n- `Exec()` method already supports running commands in containers (used for container operations)\n\n### **11. Documentation**\n\n**Location: `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`**\n- Added resume documentation section (lines 412-441)\n- Explains resume as re-attempting from specified step or first failed step\n- Details step-specific resume behavior:\n  - Script steps: Rerun fresh, prior output available\n  - Prompt steps: Resume conversation (-c flag, \"retry\" prompt)\n  - Workflow steps: Start again, pass prior step output\n- Prerequisites: run in failed state, container must exist\n- Examples: `cloche resume develop-vivid-bear-040e` and `cloche resume develop-vivid-bear-040e implement`\n\n### **12. Key Files Summary**\n\n| Component | File | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|---------|\n| Protocol | `/workspace/api/clochepb/resume.pb.go` | Message types |\n| Protocol | `/workspace/api/clochepb/resume_grpc.pb.go` | gRPC service definition |\n| Domain | `/workspace/internal/domain/resume.go` | ResumeConfig struct and helpers |\n| Engine | `/workspace/internal/engine/resume.go` | ResumeExecutor wrapper |\n| Server | `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/resume.go` | Main resume RPC handler |\n| Agent | `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | Prompt resume logic |\n| CLI | `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI command routing |\n| Agent | `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` | Resume config loading |\n| Runner | `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` | Resume integration |\n| Daemon | `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | gRPC handler registration |\n\n### **13. Resume Flow Summary**\n\n```\nUser runs: cloche resume <run-id> [step-name]\n    ↓\nCLI: cmdResume() sends ResumeRunRequest to daemon\n    ↓\nServer: ResumeRun() handler\n  - Loads failed run\n  - Identifies resume step (provided or first failed)\n  - Builds prior results map\n  - Routes to container or host resume\n    ↓\nContainer Resume:\n  - Verifies container exists\n  - Writes resume.json to container\n  - Copies updated project files\n  - Restarts container\n  - Agent reads resume.json\n  - ResumeExecutor skips prior steps\n  - ResumeStep marked with _resume flag\n  - Prompt adapter uses conversation resume (-c) for prompts\n    ↓\nRun continues from resume point to completion\n```\n\n### **14. Key Design Decisions**\n\n1. **Resume Config as File**: Uses JSON file (`resume.json`) to pass resume state into container, avoiding need to modify container startup command\n2. **Replay via Mapping**: Prior successful steps are \"executed\" by returning cached results immediately\n3. **Conversation Resume**: Prompt steps get special `-c` flag and \"retry\" prompt for Claude Code to resume conversation\n4. **State Preservation**: Keeps attempt counts and output files from previous run\n5. **Host Support**: Host runs also support resume via same ResumeConfig mechanism\n6. **Container Update**: Can copy updated scripts/prompts/overrides into stopped container before restart\n\nThis comprehensive implementation allows sophisticated recovery workflows where failed attempts can be resumed from any point, with full conversation history for prompt steps and all prior state available for script steps."}],"totalDurationMs":45915,"totalTokens":84760,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":903,"cache_read_input_tokens":80855,"output_tokens":3001,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":903},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
