ays keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche resume`\n\nResume a failed workflow run from a specified step or the first failed step.\n\n```\ncloche resume <run-id> [step-name]\n```\n\n| Argument | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `<run-id>` | The run identifier of the failed run. |\n| `[step-name]` | Optional: the step to resume from. If omitted, resumes from the first failed step. |\n\nStep-specific resume behavior:\n\n- **Script steps**: Rerun the script fresh. Updated scripts are copied into the container. Prior step output remains available.\n- **Prompt steps**: Resume the conversation instead of starting a new one. For Claude, this adds `-c` (continue) and uses \"retry\" as the prompt.\n- **Workflow steps**: Start the step again, passing values from previous steps' output.\n\nPrerequisites:\n- The run must be in a failed state.\n- For container workflows, the container must still exist (not cleaned up).\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [flags]","numLines":40,"startLine":660,"totalLines":978}}}
